# 2. Start with Basic Models and Views Before Adding Complex Features

## Recommended Development Order

### Phase 1 (Basic)

Create:

### User Model/Profile

```python
class Profile(models.Model):
    user = models.OneToOneField(User,on_delete=models.CASCADE)
    bio = models.TextField()
```

### Post Model

```python
class Post(models.Model):
    author = models.ForeignKey(User,on_delete=models.CASCADE)
    content = models.TextField()
```

Build:

* Register
* Login
* Create Post
* View Posts

Only after these work, move to:

### Phase 2

* Likes
* Comments

### Phase 3

* Friends
* Notifications

### Phase 4

* Chat
* Real-time features

This approach reduces bugs and confusion.

